    "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
    "body": "Hi all. I noticed stable channel still packaged version 0.11.5 . I think the problem is on the tree-sitter parsers installation, as seen on the logs: https://launchpadlibrarian.net/849197939/buildlog_snap_ubuntu_jammy_amd64_nvim-stable_BUILDING.txt.gz\n\nMore specifically:\n\n<img width=\"1210\" height=\"167\" alt=\"Image\" src=\"https://github.com/user-attachments/assets/a38a6b07-54de-418a-8147-66aa4ebd844f\" />\n\nIndeed, nvim-treesitter appears to have removed the command on this commit: https://github.com/nvim-treesitter/nvim-treesitter/commit/cde679e435ade757733772236abf299fc06da231\n\nBesides above changes, it appears the plugin now depends on tree-sitter-cli - stated on the docs and tested by me.\n\nI'll make a PR attempting to fix the issues, could you please review?",
