        {
            "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
            "body": "Hey Justin, please consider reopening this issue, since the problem wasn't fixed.\n\nFor the record, I did my homework - adjusted the file, ran Snapcraft on my machine and it compiled perfectly (I used to maintain a Snap package, so not entirely unfamiliar to it).\n\nSince it worked beautifully here, it SHOULD have worked on Launchpad farm (amd64 at minimum, given it was the platform I use), but there's something else going on (maybe a temporary problem?).\n\nSo, I see three possible proceeding from here:\n\n- I may create a new patch, printing nvim-treesitter install log, to see if we can identify the issue.\n- Getting rid of treesitter on the package. I agree with you, seems odd, since it's an optional component.\n- Leaving the package broken (hope you don't pick this).\n\nJust let me know what you want to do (if at all), and I'll try to help.",
